content/chapter-05/LogProcessingGrok.htm.body:
Logs Processing - Grok Filter

grok filter plugin is to parse the unstructured log data into something query-able
Log data:2017-06-21 22:18:25,276 - util.py[DEBUG]: Reading from /proc/uptime (quiet=False)

Predefined match patterns
Custom parse patterns added:For module: (?
Capture into a field:  %{TIMESTAMP_ISO8601:datetime} where datetime is a field name
Full capture pattern:%{TIMESTAMP_ISO8601:datetime}%{SPACE}%{SPACE}-%{SPACE} (?(?(.+)(?=\]))(\]: )%{GREEDYDATA:message}

Transformed data (1st log record):    {
  "datetime": "2017-06-21 22:18:25,276",
  "module": "util.py",
  "loglevel": "DEBUG",
